    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Eaux Vives Park and Paddling Pool]]></title>
    <link href="http://playdegex.github.io/2013/09/eaux-vives-park-and-paddling-pool/"/>
    <updated>2013-09-08T15:53:14+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://playdegex.github.io/2013/09/eaux-vives-park-and-paddling-pool</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="http://www.ville-geneve.ch/plan-ville/parcs-jardins-plages-bains-publics/parc-eaux-vives/">Eaux-Vives</a> park borders Lake Geneva close to the Jet d'Eau.
The park itself is beautifully kept with very impressive flower beds. On
a hot day the park has a well shaded paddling pool which is not photographed here.</p>

<p>To find the playground walk uphill to the top of the park. The cafe in the
park has ice-creams and a reasonable menu-du-jour. As well as the main
wooden climbing frame there are some easy swings for toddlers.
The day we were there free deck chairs were are also available.</p>

